rts-reference.com/cfb/schools/florida/2007-schedule.html |title=2007 Florida Gators |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003175946/http://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/florida/2007-schedule.html |archivedate=2016-10-03 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2008 Florida Gators football team|2008]]\n| Urban Meyer\n| [[2009 BCS National Championship Game|BCS National Championship Game]]\u2020\n| [[2008 Oklahoma Sooners football team|Oklahoma]]\n| '''W''' 24\u201314<ref name=uf08/>\n|-\n| [[2009 Florida Gators football team|2009]]\n| Urban Meyer\n| [[2010 Sugar Bowl|Sugar Bowl]]\u2020\n| [[2009 Cincinnati Bearcats football team|Cincinnati]]\n| '''W''' 51\u201324<ref name=uf09>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/florida/2009-schedule.html |title=2009 Florida Gators |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005074716/http://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/florida/2009-schedule.html |archivedate=2016-10-05 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2010 Florida Gators football team|2010]]\n| Urban Meyer\n| [[2011 Outback Bowl|Outback Bowl]]\n| [[2010 Penn State Nittany Lions football team|Penn State]]\n| '''W''' 37\u201324<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/florida/2010-schedule.html |title=2010 Florida Gators |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003180832/http://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/florida/2010-schedule.html |archivedate=2016-10-03 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2011 Florida Gators football team|2011]]\n| [[Will Muschamp]]\n| [[2012 Gator Bowl|Gator Bowl]]\n| [[2011 Ohio State Buckeyes football team|Ohio State]]\n| '''W''' 24\u201317<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/florida/2011-schedule.html |title=2011 Florida Gators |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003182351/http://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/florida/2011-schedule.html |archivedate=2016-10-03 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2012 Florida Gators football team|2012]]\n| Will Muschamp\n| [[2013 Sugar Bowl|Sugar Bowl]]\u2020\n| [[2012 Louisville Cardinals football team|Louisville]]\n| L 23\u201333<ref name=uf12/>\n|-\n| [[2014 Florida Gators football team|2014]]\n| [[D. J. Durkin]] (interim)\n| [[2015 Birmingham Bowl (January)|Birmingham Bowl]]\n| [[2014 East Carolina Pirates football team|East Carolina]]\n| '''W''' 28\u201320<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/florida/2014-schedule.html |title=2014 Florida Gators |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410035613/http://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/florida/2014-schedule.html |archivedate=2016-04-10 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2015 Florida Gators football team|2015]]\n| [[Jim McElwain]]\n| [[2016 Citrus Bowl (January)|Citrus Bowl]]\n| [[2015 Michigan Wolverines football team|Michigan]]\n| L 7\u201341<ref name=uf15/>\n|-\n| [[2016 Florida Gators football team|2016]]\n| Jim McElwain\n| [[2017 Outback Bowl|Outback Bowl]]\n| [[2017 Iowa Hawkeyes football team|Iowa]]\n| '''W''' 30\u20133\n|-\n| [[2018 Florida Gators football team|2018]]\n| [[Dan Mullen]]\n| [[2018 Peach Bowl (December)|Peach Bowl]]\u2020\n| [[2018 Michigan Wolverines football team|Michigan]]\n| '''W''' 41\u201315\n|-\n| [[2019 Florida Gators football team|2019]]\n| Dan Mullen\n| [[2019 Orange Bowl|Orange Bowl]]\u2020\n| [[2019 Virginia Cavaliers football team|Virginia]]\n| '''W''' 36\u201328\n|-\n|}\n* The 1912 [[Bacardi Bowl]] held in [[Havana, Cuba]] was not sanctioned by the NCAA and was intended to be one half of a two-game event which was not completed due to a dispute over the rules of the game. As such, the [[University of Florida Athletic Association]] does not include the contest in the Gators' official bowl record.<ref name=ufmediaguide/>\n\u2020 Denotes Coalition, Alliance, BCS or New Year's Six Bowl game.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Records by Bowl Game\n! style=\"background:#0021A5; color:white;\"|Bowl\n! style=\"background:#0021A5; color:white;\"|Record\n