racy.html \"Marx on Democratic Forms of Government\"]. ''Socialist Register''. pp. 101\u2013124. Retrieved 8 February 2020. \"Marx's theory moves in the direction of defining consistent democracy in socialist terms, and consistent socialism in democratic terms.\"</ref>\n* [[Erich Fromm]], Jewish German philosopher<ref>Wilde, Lawrence (2004). ''Erich Fromm and the Quest for Solidarity''. Palgrave Macmillan. p. 14. {{ISBN|978-1403961419}}.</ref><ref>Friedman, Lawrence J. (2014) [2013]. ''The Lives of Erich Fromm: Love's Prophet''. Columbia University Press. p. 236. {{ISBN|978-0231162586}}.</ref><ref>Braune, Joan (2014). ''Erich Fromm's Revolutionary Hope: Prophetic Messianism As A Critical Theory of the Future''. Rotterdam: Sense Publishers. p. 40. {{ISBN|978-94-6209-812-1}}.</ref>\n* [[Charles Fourier]], French philosopher and utopian socialist{{sfn|Sargent|2008|p=118}}\n* [[Henry George]], American social reformer{{sfn|Sargent|2008|p=118}}\n* [[Charles Hall (economist)|Charles Hall]], \u00a0British physician, social critic and [[Ricardian socialist]]<ref>Dinwiddy, J. R. (August 1976). [https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/international-review-of-social-history/article/charles-hall-early-english-socialist/B318871BCE7478DED39FC42F9C255A3D \"Charles Hall, Early English Socialist\"]. ''International Review of Social History''. '''21''' (2): 256\u2013276. {{doi|10.1017/S002085900000523X}}. \"Hall (in common with several other pioneers of socialism and democracy [...].\"</ref>\n* [[Christopher Hitchens]], English-American journalist<ref>{{cite web|last=Intellect|first=Manufacturing|title=Christopher Hitchens interview on the Clintons (1999)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hlrM0Siszq8|publisher=YouTube|accessdate=14 October 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Owen Jones]], English journalist and political commentator<ref>Jones, Owen (30 October 2015). [https://www.twitter.com/owenjones84/status/395576194038382592 \"Modern capitalism is a sham, and why democratic socialism is our only hope\"]. Twitter. Retrieved 30 October 2015.</ref>\n* [[Helen Keller]], American political activist<ref>{{cite web|last=Keller|first=Helen|title=How I Became a Socialist|url=https://www.marxists.org/reference/archive/keller-helen/works/1910s/12_11_03.htm|publisher=Marxists Internet Archive|accessdate=15 June 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Martin Luther King Jr.]], African-American [[Civil rights movement|civil rights]] leader<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Sturm|first1=Douglas|title=Martin Luther King, Jr., as Democratic Socialist|journal=The Journal of Religious Ethics|date=1990|volume=18|issue=2|pages=79\u2013105|jstor=40015109|quote=The essay argues that King was in fact a democratic socialist [...].}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Sekou|first=Osagyefo Uhuru|title=The radical gospel of Martin Luther King|url=http://america.aljazeera.com/opinions/2014/1/martin-luther-kingsocialismantiimperialism.html|agency=[[Al Jazeera]]|date=20 January 2014|quote=King's democratic socialism [...].}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Hendricks|first=Obery M.|title=The Uncompromising Anti-Capitalism of Martin Luther King Jr.|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/obery-m-hendricks-jr-phd/the-uncompromising-anti-capitalism-of-martin-luther-king-jr_b_4629609.html|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|date=20 January 2014|quote=For King the answer was democratic socialism.}}</ref>\n* [[Naomi Klein]], Canadian author and social activist<ref>Nineham, Chris (2007). [http://www.socialistreview.org.uk/article.php?articlenumber=10110 ''The Shock Doctrine'' Book Review]. ''Socialist Review''. Retrieved 11 August 2013.</ref>\n* [[Leszek Ko\u0142akowski]], Polish philosopher and communist dissident<ref>Falk, Barbara J. (2003). ''Dilemmas of Dissidence in East-Central Europe: Citizen Intellectuals and Philosopher Kings''. Central European University Press. p. 157. \"[Leszek Ko\u0142akowski] was increasingly critical of the Marxism institutionalized by the party-state, drawing his inspiration from the newly published writings of the \"