lish-born American philosopher and political theorist<ref name=\"Monahan\">Monahan, Sean (6 March 2015). [https://www.jacobinmag.com/2015/03/thomas-paine-american-revolution-common-sense/ \"Reading Paine From the Left\"]. ''Jacobin''. Retrieved 13 February 2020.</ref> Their concern for both [[democracy]] and [[social justice]] marked them out as key precursors of democratic socialism.<ref name=\"Thompson\">Thompson, E. P. (1963). ''The Making of the English Working Class''. Victor Gollancz Ltd.</ref>\n* [[Bertrand Russell]], British philosopher<ref>{{cite book|title=Bertrand Russell: A Political Life|last=Ryan|first=Alan|publisher=Macmillan|year=1981|isbn=9780374528201|page=87|quote=None the less Russell joined the ILP [Independent Labour Party] and declared himself a democratic socialist, then and thereafter.}}</ref>\n* [[Andrei Sakharov]], Soviet physicist, [[Soviet dissident|dissident]] and [[human rights]] activist<ref>{{cite web|title=Andrei Sakharov|url=http://spartacus-educational.com/COLDsakharov.htm|publisher=[[Spartacus Educational]]|quote=He also advocated the integration of the communist and capitalist systems to form what he called democratic socialism.}}</ref>\n* [[Henri de Saint-Simon]], French political and economic utopian socialist theorist{{sfn|Sargent|2008|p=118}}\n* [[Roger Waters]], English musician<ref>{{cite web|last1=Greene|first1=Andy|title=Roger Waters on 'The Wall,' Socialism and His Next Concept Album|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/roger-waters-on-the-wall-socialism-and-his-next-concept-album-20151102|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=17 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Richard D. Wolff]], American economist<ref>[http://www.rdwolff.com/content/young-democratic-socialists-interview-professor-richard-wolff \"Young Democratic Socialists: Interview With Professor Richard Wolff\"]. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150909065143/http://www.rdwolff.com/content/young-democratic-socialists-interview-professor-richard-wolff|date=