our-britain/401492/|title=How Jeremy Corbyn Would Govern Britain|last=Calamur|first=Krishnadev|date=18 August 2015|work=[[The Atlantic]]|accessdate=17 September 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Anthony Crosland]], member of the Labour Party{{sfn|Page|2007|p=}}<ref name=\"Freeden, Sargent & Stears\">Freeden, Michael; Sargent, Lyman Tower; Stears, Marc, eds. (15 August 2013). ''The Oxford Handbook of Political Ideologies''. OUP Oxford. p. 356. {{ISBN|978-0199585977}}.</ref>\n* [[Eugene V. Debs]], [[Perennial candidate|five-time]] [[Socialist Party of America]] presidential candidate{{sfn|Draper|1966|loc=\"Chapter 8: The 100% American Scene\"|p=}}\n* [[Tommy Douglas]], father of [[Medicare (Canada)|Medicare]]<ref name=\"Lovick\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.ca/en/article/tommy-douglas/|title=Tommy Douglas|last=Lovick|first=L. D.|date=30 September 2013|website=The Canadian Encyclopedia|accessdate=13 February 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Evan Durbin]], member of the Labour Party{{sfn|Picard|1985|p=}}\n* [[Michael Foot]], leader of the Labour Party and Leader of the Opposition<ref>Wilson, Cristopher (5 December 2013). ''Understanding A/S Level Government Politics''. Manchester University Press. p. 150. {{ISBN|978-0-7190-6081-6}}.</ref>\n* [[Peter Hain]], member of the Labour Party{{sfn|Hain|1995|p=}}<ref>{{cite book|last=Hain|first=Peter|year=2015|title=Back to the Future of Socialism|publisher=Bristol University Press|isbn=978-1447321682|jstor=j.ctt1t8979r}}</ref>\n* [[Michael Harrington]], founder of the [[Democratic Socialists of America]]{{sfn|Picard|1985|p=}}{{sfn|Steger|1997|p=}}\n* [[Denis Healey]], member of the Labour Party<ref name=\"NS Corbyn\">{{cite news|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/2015/08/im-no-bennite-im-increasingly-tempted-jeremy-corbyn|title=I'm no Bennite. But I'm increasingly tempted by Jeremy Corbyn|last=Ryan|first=Craig||work=[[New Statesman]]|date=17 August 2015|accessdate=30 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yorkvision.co